---INSTALL---
If you want to have less trouble as possible follow these steps:

0) ensure that mod_rewrite is working
1) copy the JBEdit folder in your Apache public dir
2) open the php/frame_gen.php and php/JBEdit.php files and edit the JBEdit_dir define to follow your needs
3) open the file .htaccess and put the correct RewriteBase directory
4) put a video called video.mp4 in the downloaded/ directory
5) give all permissions to downloaded/ and frames/ directories or change the ownership to www-data:www-data (or whatever...)
6) go with your browser to the JBEdit dir and enjoy!

After extraction wait the time of extraction and then you should find a new EXTRACTED_video.mp4 in the downloaded/ dir, or follow the link on the page.

For any problem or question: m.giacco@gmail.com 
I will be very pleased to help you using JBEdit! If you need some help integrating JBEdit in you project I'm very glad to try helping you! Don't hesitate to contact me!
Happy hacking!

